And some are waiting for a collapse.
But no matter how some Republicans try to drag Donald Trump down from the top of the polls, it hasn't (yet) worked.
Ten of the last 11 national polls have shown Donald Trump leading by double digits, and some are beginning to seriously question what it means for the real estate mogul's chances of winning the nomination.
Of course, it is too early in the parliamentary term.
